Subject: [PATCH 4689/4706] ASoC: rt298: remove idle_bias_off = true

commit ef6e34fcff726885ce3df9867f1ee8ce1b27ebe1 from
git://git.yoctoproject.org/linux-yocto-4.1

Codec will not go into suspend if there is any widget forced on with
idle_bias_off true. We want codec go into suspend when the system is
suspend. Also, we don't do anything in bias level OFF case. So it is
actually no different in bias level STANDBY or OFF case.

Change-Id: Ifbc222892c03375fb440d807a683142b3562d8d6
Signed-off-by: Bard Liao <bardliao@realtek.com>
Reviewed-on: https://git-gar-1.devtools.intel.com/gerrit/10664
Reviewed-by: Jayanti, Satya Charitardha <satya.charitardha.jayanti@intel.com>
Tested-by: Jayanti, Satya Charitardha <satya.charitardha.jayanti@intel.com>
---
 sound/soc/codecs/rt298.c |    1 -
 1 files changed, 0 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/codecs/rt298.c b/sound/soc/codecs/rt298.c
index 6ded3fb..9fd4bbb 100644
--- a/sound/soc/codecs/rt298.c
+++ b/sound/soc/codecs/rt298.c
@@ -1096,7 +1096,6 @@ static struct snd_soc_codec_driver soc_codec_dev_rt298 = {
 	.suspend = rt298_suspend,
 	.resume = rt298_resume,
 	.set_bias_level = rt298_set_bias_level,
-	.idle_bias_off = true,
 	.controls = rt298_snd_controls,
 	.num_controls = ARRAY_SIZE(rt298_snd_controls),
 	.dapm_widgets = rt298_dapm_widgets,
